page.title: 03Ecology 2
page.content: During the summer you see many butterflies including painted lady,red admiral, peacock, small tortoishell, cabbage white, small blue and orange tip. There are many other different insects living on the wide range of plant life in our district. There is mixed farming in this area and you will see grass, wheat, barley and potatoes growing in fields. The grasses we found growing along the brook are couch, rye, fescues, meadow grasses and cocks foot.In some of the fields there are rooks of thistles. In the hedges grow poppies, wild roses and horsetails. The trees are mainly oak, sycamore, ash, poplar, pussy willow and elder.There are at least six badger sets near the village and lots of foxes and once they stole the school hens so we got some more.
